LOCUS       HIV_pTI                 6887 bp ds-DNA     circular     10-FEB-2026
DEFINITION  .
COMMENT     HIV_RT expression under pT7_Lac0 promoter (i.e. It has a Lac0 box
            to improve the promoter repression).  This system drives the
            expression of HIV_RT in the presence of RNAT7 polymerase (which
            typically is induced by IPTG in E.coli BL21). Kanamycin Resistant
            pBR322 ORI + ROP (middle/low copy plasmid)
            pT7_Lac0::Riboj54_B0034_His_tag::GS_linker::HIV_RT::3xStop::Tz in
            pTI tagged HIVRT translation information: LacI and HIVRT Sequences
            confirmed by sequencing (Col 1) LacI translation rate from 4valine
            : 2275.31 accord to RBS calculator. 66KDa subunit of HIV RT can be
            expressed in E. coli and dimerized giving a functional homolog
            https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4441793/#R40 and
            Restle T, Müller B, Goody RS. Dimerization of human
            immunodeficiency virus type 1 reverse transcriptase. A target for
            chemotherapeutic intervention. Journal of Biological Chemistry.
            1990 Jun 5;265(16):8986-8. part from this vector
            https://benchling.com/s/seq-59c1HZx7CtujhlH1qco7 from Bryan C.
            Dickinson l;b
